SIMPLE: wormil
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wormil
<hw>Wor"mil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. 1st
<er>Warble</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any botfly larva which burrows in
or beneath the skin of domestic and wild animals, thus producing sores.
They belong to various species of <gen>Hypoderma</gen> and allied
genera. Domestic cattle are often infested by a large species. See
<er>Gadfly</er>. Called also <altname>warble</altname>, and
<altname>worble</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>wormal</asp>,
<asp>wormul</asp>, and <asp>wornil</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>See 1st <er>Warble</er>, 1
<sd>(b)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wormling</ent>⟦br⟧
